  <h1>Chicken Recipes (and Turkey, too) </h1>
  <p>Lots of people are intimidated by the idea of roasting a whole chicken, but it's really quite easy. Rather than a single recipe, I wrote up a few variations in this article on <a href="articles/how-to-roast-a-chicken.htm">how to roast a chicken</a>. If you're cooking up a turkey, I've got a few ideas as well, including one recipe where you <a href="Recipes/turkey-recipe-turnabout.htm">turn the turkey around a few times</a> and another where you <a href="Recipes/turkey-recipe-cheesecloth.htm">cook the turkey covered in a cheesecloth soaked in wine and butter</a>. </p>
  <p>And if you just want to add some flavor to plain chicken pieces, try some of these <a href="Recipes/chicken-marinades.htm">chicken marinade recipes</a>.</p>
  <p>Here's how to make <a href="Recipes/turkey-gravy.htm">turkey gravy</a> too. Follow the same basic steps for chicken gravy of course.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="Recipes/baked-crispy-chicken.htm">Baked Crispy Chicken Breasts</a></li>
